# Core Coding Standards

Use these defaults for maintainability, security, and long-term stability.

## Tech and architecture defaults

- Next.js + React + TypeScript.
- SCSS/Sass for styling (no Tailwind).
- UI-only baseline via `@drkaachen/design-system-ui`.
- CMS/runtime integration only when explicitly needed.

## Dependencies

- Prefer platform features and small focused utilities.
- Add dependencies only when they are actively maintained and clearly justified.
- Avoid hidden "magic" abstractions that reduce debuggability.

## Code quality

- Keep functions small and single-purpose.
- Favor explicit, readable logic over clever abstractions.
- Use descriptive names for symbols and files.
- Keep comments in sync with behavior.

## Security and privacy

- Treat all external input as untrusted and validate it.
- Never hardcode secrets or commit tokens.
- Avoid logging personal data unless justified and documented.

## Testing and docs

- Update or add tests for behavior changes.
- Update docs when APIs, env vars, architecture, or security posture changes.
